query.result:
1 While thus along the edge, one before the other, 2 we went our way, and often the good master 3 said to me: "Look out: it profits you that I make you shrewd";
4 the sun was striking me on my right shoulder, 5 which, with its rays, was already changing all the west 6 from a white aspect to a light blue;
7 and I, with my shadow, made the flame 8 seem more glowing; and yet by such an indication 9 I saw many shades, as we went, taking heed.

